      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/779978/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-15T07:12:08.440Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>Just started using the app and wondering why when creating a plan with CJ I have most of my long days workouts splitted in 2 (the second workout being a \u201ccontinued\u201d version of the first one). Is it to allow for \u201cskipping\u201d the second workout in case time is missing? Or to be able to have 2 workouts at different time of day (lunch and evening for example)?</p>\n<p>Also, I find the long workouts are very long, sometimes 2h30 when my week is 4 workouts and the other ones are &lt;45min. It would be nice to have a way to specify what is the longest time available for these, especially when selecting the \u201cindoor\u201d option. I do not see myself seating on my trainer for 2h+, and I primarily don\u2019t have this time available. I would rather have all my workouts between 45min-1h, and maybe 1h30 for the long ones, something more smoothed, and easier to fit in a busy schedule.</p>",
